Other Dow Jones










KKR earnings rise as portfolio, fees grow
KKR & Co.'s second-quarter profit surged as its portfolio appreciated and transaction fees increased. For the period ended June 30, the New York private-equity firm's earnings rose to $405.6 million, or 81 cents a share, from $93.9 million, or 19 cents a share, the same period a year earlier. Economic profit, a closely watched performance measure that reflects unrealized investment gains, rose to $752.5 million, or 89 cents a share, from $191.2 million, or 23 cents a share, a year earlier.

Jul. 27, 2017 at 6:46 a.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com










