Jun. 1, 2017 at 10:41 p.m. ET
by Julie Steinberg 









Carlyle earnings lifted by private-equity gains
Carlyle Group LP's first-quarter earnings rose on appreciation in its private equity and other investments. For the period ended March 31, the Washington, D.C., asset manager's profit rose to $83 million, or 90 cents a share, from $8.4 million, or a penny a share, in the year-earlier period. Economic net income, a closely tracked performance measure that reflects unrealized investment gains, rose to $364.6 million, or $1.09 a share, from $58.2 million, or 18 cents a share, a year earlier.

May. 3, 2017 at 7:28 a.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com










